# CVEs deferred to upstream tesserix base-image refresh.
#
# These live in the alpine 3.23.4 base layer of ghcr.io/tesserix/base-nginx-spa
# (and base-go-builder etc.). Patching them here via `apk upgrade` in the app
# Dockerfile is not viable because nginx-package upgrades reset
# /etc/nginx/conf.d and /var/cache/nginx ownership to root, breaking the
# non-root container user that the helm chart enforces (runAsUser: 1001).
# The proper fix is a base-image rebuild on the latest alpine — out of scope
# for this app repo.
#
# Risk assessment for HomeChef:
# - CVE-2026-27135 (nghttp2 HTTP/2 DoS): Cloudflare terminates HTTP/2 at the
#   edge before reaching our nginx, so the nghttp2 code path is not exposed
#   to untrusted client traffic.
# - CVE-2026-34743 (xz buffer overflow on malformed .xz indexing): xz is
#   not invoked on user-supplied data anywhere in the SPA serving path.
# - CVE-2026-4367 (PDF.js / generic): not applicable to SPA bundle.

CVE-2026-27135
CVE-2026-34743
CVE-2026-4367
